  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Stoma surgery is a relatively common treatment for patients suffering from colorectal
      diseases.This study aimed to investigate the impact on hospital stay and short-term overall
      complications prior to and following the introduction of an outpatient preoperative stoma
      education program.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      38 patients undergoing stoma surgery were analyzed, 73 prior education program and 65
      following it.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
